Ranch Oyster Crackers

Preheat oven to 250F

- 1oz ranch seasoning
Can be made by combining: 2 Tbsp buttermilk powder, 1/2 tsp parsley, 1/4 tsp dill, 1/4 tsp onion powder, 1/8 tsp garlic powder, 1/4 tsp lemon pepper, 1/8 tsp sugar, 1/8 tsp salt, 1/8 tsp pepper

- 1/2 cup butter
Melt butter in small saucepan

- 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 1/2 tsp red pepper flakes
+ ranch seasoning
Add ingredients to melter butter and whisk to combine

- 10 oz oyster crackers
In a large bowl, drizzle the butter mixture over the crackers and stir with a rubber spatula until evenly coated.

Line a baking sheet with parchment. Spread crackers on the sheet, and bake for 10 minutes.

Stir the crackers and redistribute evenly. Bake for another 10 minutes.

